France and the rest of Europe in the focus of investors.
On Tuesday, a statistical storm blew through Europe.
The individual countries published their data on their GDP for the third quarter.
The Czech economy stagnated compared to the previous quarter, while Germany and France grew.
The bond market is breaking all records.
Investors are not only keeping an eye on Greece, but now also on Spain, France, Austria and other countries.
