The menu of a fatty child: It does not have breakfast and eats sausage for dinner
More than a third of children aged 9 to 13 have problems with obesity, with 9 percent of all students and 5 percent of all children being overweight.
Recent surveys have shown that obese children mostly come from families with unhealthy lifestyles.
This shows once again how important the environment in which a person grows up is for healthy development and the examples that surround him are.
On the tables of obese children, sausages are up to half more often on the table than in families in which normal-weight children live.
More than 19 percent of overweight children had French fries for dinner on the eve of the awareness campaign under the motto "Adiposity is not a coincidence".
In families with fatties, sport is not one of their favorite activities, which also affects the majority of today's students - only 15 percent responded that their parents find time for active exercise at least once a week.
Survey of 900 children
The survey took place last year towards the end of the school year, with nearly 900 children from primary schools across the Czech Republic being interviewed.
This was already the second year of the "Adiposity is not a coincidence" campaign, which is supported by the Allgemeine Krankenkasse and the Unilever company.
To date, more than 12 thousand students from 4th and 8th grades have participated in the project.
Unhealthy diet and lack of exercise in the family are decisive factors that are responsible for the frighteningly increasing number of children with overweight or even obesity.
"For example, only half of the children surveyed said they ate breakfast-second breakfast-lunch-vesper-evening five times a day - one of the main requirements for a healthy diet," says one of the survey results.
No breakfast and sausage for dinner
Experts point out that even relative trifles, such as the family’s regular breakfast time, are important for a child’s healthy development.
In the Czech Republic, however, only 23 percent of the families of the students eat breakfast.
And in most families, everyone eats breakfast on their own.
Worst of all was the finding that in one in ten families, there was no breakfast at all.
Breakfast is the cornerstone of a healthy daily diet.
The survey test showed, among other things, that in the families of overweight children you consume unhealthy fries much more often.
And almost everyone – regardless of weight – drinks sweet lemonades every day (70 percent)
Although more than 40 percent of the children surveyed exercise, only less than half of their parents do – only 15 percent.
Create your own menu
Another part of the survey allowed selected children (204 boys and 172 girls from 13 schools) to put together their own meal plan based on opportunities offered according to appetite and opinion.
"What Czech children between 12 and 15 prefer in terms of nutrition is far from the ideal of a healthy diet.
Among her favorite dishes were many pastries, meat dishes and, of course, sweets.
"The great popularity of sweet lemonades is alarming in particular," the final report on this survey emphasizes.
At lunch, the main dish, pasta won just before poultry.
Legumes the children almost did not like and the popularity of fish and vegetable dishes for lunch was very low.
Return to Health
At the same time, the survey also showed that the children are quite willing to change their eating habits if they get the right information.
"In many cases, the control group of survey participants who completed the questionnaire after the conclusion of the enlightening lecture "Adiposity is not a coincidence", there was a marked shift in preferences towards principles of healthy nutrition," the results of the project are cited.
This was evident, for example, in the sweet limos, where many children began to give priority to ordinary water.
The children also checked poultry or fish much more often in the questionnaire as the main course of the day and were willing to eat less dumplings or sweet foods.
Professionals claim - a stylist must also be a good psychologist
In the introductory article on how stylists learn, I had a bit of a muffled feeling that this was a bit too much stuff to start with.
I didn’t know in the slightest what was to come.
Lectures by three professionals from the industry, the clothing of problematic figures and a seminar on how the "on the square" works.
It's supposed to get worse.
The closer the exam gets, the more information and practical tasks we have to deal with.
But even if the course takes place every Saturday and Sunday, it is still fully booked.
This time we debated with director Alena (not a single man participates in the course) how to attract a woman who does not have an ideally proportioned figure.
After all, most of us are.
Some have a too short neck, the others a too boyish figure without proper curves and still others are chubby.
It is up to the stylist to visually conceal wide shoulders, lengthen the neck or conjure up the necessary curves.
We also got tips on how to attract a woman like Jennifer Lopez - with a big bust, wide hip and narrow waist - pretty and figure-hugging, without making her seem too provocative.
For example, if the difference between the waist and hips is so big that the skirt or pants really do not fit, you should at least have a piece tailor-made.
You will not regret it, because well-fitting clothes are simply priceless.
In such a tailor-made skirt you feel much better than in a bar that always slips up and down, stands out at the waist, etc.
Boyish figures can in turn allow themselves to wear clothing with pleats, puffs, appliques, embroidery or gathering.
With this amount of information and figure types, I’m glad that I have a whole week to let everything go through my head thoroughly.
And yet I am afraid that it is almost impossible in view of the assigned homework.
Each of the course participants was assigned a celebrity, for which she should come up with suitable outfits - daywear and evening gown.
In doing so, we should take into account the current appearance, the fashion style of the corresponding star and his figure type.
I'm supposed to "dress" Miranda Kerr, whom you may know from the Victoria's Secret campaign.
I cheer inside, because that’s much better for me personally than, for example, wearing Britney Spears or Christina Aguilera, who has probably gained a hundred kilos recently (well, that’s a bit exaggerated), or even the young Selena Gomez.
We should cut the garments out of magazines or search the internet, print them out and then edit them graphically.
In the "moodboard", as the whole result is called, our very personal style and our relationship to graphic design should be expressed.
It is very important to also think about the graphic side of the styling.
The stylist not only attracts the models purely physically, but also designs the so-called product page in the journals (according to specific specifications, for example trend handbags, coats, etc.).
Stylist and designer Mario Kamen<0xC3><0xAD>k told us about this.
But not until Sunday.
This means that a stylist must have a good overall overview.
The Saturday lecture, filled with information about figure types, was immediately seasoned by three visitors from the industry:
by stylist Jan Pokorn<0xC3><0xBD>, fashion designer Jakub Polanka and fashion photographer Ben Ren<0xC4><0x8D>.
Jakub reminded us that fashion is illusion and that a stylist should be able to take advantage of it.
And a skilled stylist is able to work with a single piece of clothing in very different ways.
The magic word is variability.
For example, you can wear a trench coat as usual over the jeans, like a T-shirt or coat, but you can also wear it on the naked body, put on heels and wear it as a dress.
It is enough to roll up the sleeves or the collar and the whole look looks completely different.
“Play with it,” he said.
But the most important advice to me was: "First you have to know the rules perfectly."
"Only then can you hurt her," said Jakub.
I finally realize why we have to cram all these teachings, what you can combine with what and why, even if you often get to see completely different things in fashion journals.
Not to mention fashion shows.
Thanks to photographer Ben, I now know that a stylist must have prepared many more clothing variants than he ultimately photographs.
So for a fashion story with ten pages (i.e. ten outfits) you have to be prepared to style at least fifteen.
And also that the clothing in the photo in combination with other accessories sometimes looks quite different than in reality.
So you have to expect all this in the design of the outfit.
Jan Pokorn<0xC3><0xBD> also confirmed that image and style sometimes account for half of the success.
All you have to do is look at Madonna, a not exactly brilliant singer, from whom image and marketing have made a world star.
In the Czech Republic, the services of a stylist are more reserved.
Even well-known personalities often think this is money thrown out (the main thing is that I bring something that I look like is secondary).
And if anyone can be styled by us, then we should expect that he or she will most likely impose on us a completely different (smaller) size than he or she actually needs.
Then you only need to google afterwards, in order to determine with certainty that the tabloid press writes, the corresponding celebrity has again increased or decreased, etc.
Jan and Mario told us on Sunday not to believe that a stylist only needs to focus on fashion and then "assemble" the outfit.
In his work, he has to communicate primarily with the people he styles and he has to be a smart psychologist.
Assessing people without indulging in and standing up for his opinion.
"If any manager orders us to sift through her closet and add some pretty pieces, we can't just clear out the whole closet and say, 'Oh, my God, that's awful.'
“You have to find at least a few commendable things to recommend what you can wear,” says Mario.
He also showed us very concretely what such a so-called "place bag" must contain.
So this is a bag that you button on at the waist and in which you carry all the necessary proprieties with you.
In addition to such clear items as scissors, hair removal dispensers or safety pins, it also contains such utensils as a nylon thread (this helps the stylist to photograph products, such as handbags or hats), special clips with which the clothes are gathered at the back, if it is too large (pins or other clamps are prohibited, so that the fabric does not break, of course).
But in order not only to listen, but also to try something practical, we learned how to properly slip on shoes.
Even when photographing in the studio, where the floor is level, you can damage the sole of the shoe, let alone the outside.
O we were glued and glued...
With the scissors you can not even touch the shoes, so that you do not damage them.
So you have to be really skillful.
Mario delighted me by praising my "creation" without restrictions.
The skill mentioned is not exactly my strength.
All of this was just a fraction of what we got to hear at the second weekend continuation course.
One thing has become clear to me in the meantime - to devote oneself to styling on a professional level is no child’s play.
V Need for Speed: "The Run" - the illegal race across America
Rezension
The initially carefree journey becomes an early-shift routine through a series of completely avoidable, dilettantic errors.
It was possible to fulfill the ambitions to a large extent, but what use is that, when obviously nobody wanted to do a little more.
Even before he came to the counters, the new part with the subtitle "The Run" aroused high expectations.
He promised to move the already old game series "Need for Speed" again a piece into a new dimension and in the playable demonstration examples he actually did not seem to be just one of many action racing games.
We were also curious about the fitting passages, in which the main protagonist gets out of the car and continues on foot.
But as you are already used to with NFS, in the end, much is different than you expected.
Sure - potentially quite decent arcade races, but overall the game is tempered by some superfluous flaws that have been present in this series for more or less a few years.
So they are actually no longer mistakes, but rather signs of a basically incomprehensible laziness of the game developers.
The adventure starts very well.
For the first time, you are introduced to the story, whose main character Jack has certain problems of a personal character; the only solution seems to be to participate in an illegal race across America.
In San Francisco, on the west coast, you sit at the steering wheel - with the task of being the first in New York.
The basic idea contains a whole series of interesting elements.
The entire route is divided into ten stages and more than fifty individual races.
This means that each race is held on a different track and that the individual stages take place in different, sufficiently different and interesting milieus.
One does not have a moment’s impression that the game would always offer the same thing.
Some environments are also very nice to look at, although the technical level of the graphics does not go beyond that of the earlier parts of the series.
So nothing world-moving.
But the drive through the desert, through autumnal landscape or high up through deep snowy landscape seems visually very pleasant.
From time to time, atypical elements bring a little variety to the individual races.
In the desert, for example, one is surprised by a desert storm, which severely restricts the view.
In the mountains, on the other hand, you have to take care that you are not spilled by an avalanche.
By the way, the individual races are installed quite well in succession.
Only a few, but they are enough.
For a while you try to overtake the prescribed number of opponents (in principle a classic race), then you have time to catch up (classic race against the stopwatch), then you expect a personal duel with a single opponent.
And the police are also intervening, who want to screw up the whole thing.
A novelty are passages in which Jack leaves the car.
It is more about certain interactive animations in which Jack flees from someone and where the player has to help him by pressing the right button at the right moment.
So nothing complicated.
It is surprising, however, that there are far fewer such passages in the game than one would expect (in concrete terms, probably only three).
In the end, this is more of an advantage, because at least this element has no chance of getting boring - it is one of the elements that make the game more varied in the context of the above.
The driving model follows in the footsteps of the preceding parts.
That is, from today's point of view, it does not tear out trees, on the other hand, one could not claim that it would be bad.
If you are looking for realistic simulations, you have to look elsewhere.
But the local driving model continues to do quite well for an action-packed racing, although you could find better ones in the competition.
Until then, everything is in perfect order.
Real problems only appear after a certain time.
In contrast to the driving model, the collision model is not quite O.K.
It is hard to expect a game of this kind to calculate complicated deformations and collisions, but if you have virtually no idea how the car behaves before impacting any object, then obviously not everything is okay.
Typical example: When overtaking or driving past oncoming cars, you "strive" the other car only slightly in some places, but in another, almost identical situation you get into the spin and turn wild pirouettes.
Or drive the car straight to scrap.
Thanks to the restart system, this does not matter anymore, it is always annoying.
The restarts are solved in this way: if you have total damage or land far off the track, then the game throws you back to the last clue of the track.
Only - in every race you have only five restarts.
Once you have exhausted them, everything starts all over again.
So the restarts are more like a tool, in case something does not work, but you should rather not rely on it.
Sometimes even the restart doesn't help, because nothing helps but to learn the critical section from the head.
It is extremely unpleasant that the same things often happen in the same places.
Some curves, for example, you have to drive through in a very specific way, otherwise you simply do not fit through.
Elsewhere, you always encounter "civil" cars in the same configuration, whether you are first or fifth, five seconds earlier or a minute later.
This is especially annoying in situations when you see the opponent passing two cars in front of you, but until you get there yourself, the cars are already in such a position that you have to drive them around or brake them.
And it doesn’t matter when you get there, everything is designed in such a way that this situation always comes close to your nose.
The opponents have other advantages.
In the whole game there are a few places where you are always overtaken by the same opponent in the same place and again without regard to the time.
At the end of the game on the long bridge you pass in the opposite direction.
The opponent obviously has to overtake one here on the devil come out.
And if he is already in front of you, then of course he takes the view, so that you initially drive your own car a few times in Klump.
Sure - you just want to make the game more exciting and exciting but this intention is so clear that you quickly miss the joy of the game.
And that is a pity, because despite a simpler driving model, the game is overall quite entertaining and in places also so action-packed that you almost do not know where your head stands.
And in principle, no matter what "guilt" is about it - the concept with fifty unique routes, the arrangement of the races in a way that no boredom can arise, or something completely different...
An unusual idea is also the car change in the course of the races.
You should not overlook the petrol stations on the track, because it is here that you can change the car, although in most cases the car you have is sufficient.
The cars are divided into three categories.
The sports cars are well suited for urban areas, the strong American limousines for the straight highways and exotic super sports cars for the technical rides, for example on the serpentines in the mountains.
Hand in hand with the mode of the game history also goes the task mode (challenges) - i.e. the races in the individual locations that you know from the history.
There are not only medals, but also experience points to win for your own profile, which is common for the tasks (challenges) and history.
To get to the higher driver level, various items must be unlocked: from the car started, to the backgrounds for the profile.
This is at the same time connected to the online function Autolog, which, among other things, compares its own achieved results with those of other players and also provides for further collective functions.
One of other incomprehensible carvings is a situation in the last race in history.
Here you get by car into a subway tunnel (meinetwegen), where you ride in the dark on the rails for a long time (meinetwegen).
On the speedometer, figures between 150 and 200 km/h (my way around), but there suddenly comes from behind a subway and drives one uncompromisingly to scrap.
In our editorial office, we will probably argue for a long time whether this was a blackout of the game designers or whether the authors think we are so stupid.
The technical side is nothing overwhelming but at least the overall visual impression is quite appealing in most cases and even brilliant here and there.
All the more annoying is that at some exciting moments the refresh rate slows down and this sometimes quite dramatically.
However, this applies in particular to accidents with a larger number of participants, where a continuous FPS is of no use anyway.
The sound reproduction is OK so far and the soundtrack is a matter of taste.
In an effort to appeal to young audiences on a scale as wide as possible, a soundtrack was created a l<0xC3><0xA1> "something from everyone" - but who buys such a game because of the music?!
The overall impression of Need for Speed: The Run? The feelings are rather mixed.
If the game were not diminished by the totally unnecessary mistakes mentioned, we could have claimed with the breast tone of conviction that The Run is the best piece of NFS in recent years.
This is how the game seems unfinished.
In itself a great pleasure, but you should be prepared for these mistakes to catch your eye with the power of airport headlights.
