Ten months after an armed man shot at her at close range during an election event in Tucson, Arizona, Republican Gabrielle Gifffords appeared on national television Monday night singing alone to the Broadway play "The Sun Will Come Out Tomorrow" and saying the desire to recover was greater than the desire to return to Congress.
