ADB urges Asia to help save eurozone
The Asian Development Bank (ADB) calls on India and China to support the bailout of the eurozone in its severe debt crisis in order to prevent a long-term downward trend that will slow the growth of Asia’s economy.
Rajat Nag, ADB’s administrative director based in Manila, said the two fastest-growing economies in the world must do “everything in their power” to accelerate the recovery of the currency bloc either through the International Monetary Fund or through direct mutual agreements.
